            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EJust%20as%20Satan%20was%20cast%20like%20lightning%20out%20of%20heaven%2C%20he%20is%20being%20cast%20out%20of%20his%20earthly%20kingdom%20by%20the%20power%20of%20Jesus.%20As%20Isaiah%20says%2C%20%22The%20oppressor%20will%20come%20to%20an%20end%2C%20and%20destruction%20will%20cease%3B%20the%20aggressor%20will%20vanish%20from%20the%20land%22%20(Isaiah%2016%3A4%20NIV).%20Isaiah%20further%20prophesied%20that%20in%20love%20a%20throne%20would%20be%20established%2C%20that%20in%20faithfulness%20a%20man%20from%20the%20house%20of%20David%20would%20sit%20on%20that%20throne%2C%20judging%20with%20justice%20and%20righteousness%20(v.%205).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThank%20God%20for%20the%20power%20of%20love%20over%20hatred!%20%22For%20God%20so%20loved%20the%20world%20that%20He%20gave%20his%20only%20Son.%20.%20.%20.%22(John%203%3A16).%20The%20love%20of%20God%20was%20manifested%20to%20this%20world%20the%20moment%20Jesus%20stepped%20into%20it.%20Everywhere%20He%20went%2C%20the%20oppressor's%20kingdom%20came%20to%20an%20end.%20Jesus%20cast%20out%20devils%20from%20all%20those%20bound%20by%20them%2C%20%22for%20God%20was%20with%20him%22%20(Acts%2010%3A38).%20Paul%20states%20that%20Jesus%20%22died%20for%20our%20sins%2C%20just%20as%20God%20our%20Father%20planned%2C%20in%20order%20to%20rescue%20us%20from%20this%20evil%20world%20in%20which%20we%20live%22%20(Galatians%201%3A4).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EIn%20your%20darkest%20oppression%2C%20there%20is%20One%20whom%20God%20has%20sent%20to%20rescue%20you.%20He%20is%20the%20King%20on%20the%20throne%20of%20David.%20Let%20Him%20wrap%20His%20arms%20of%20love%20around%20you%20and%20protect%2C%20deliver%2C%20and%20rescue%20you%20from%20the%20oppressor.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
